X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Mickey's Black Box": "https://mickeysblackbox.com/event/solar-federation-a-tribute-to-rush/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:mickeysblackbox
X-SOURCE:Mickey's Black Box
X-SOURCE-URL:https://mickeysblackbox.com/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260328T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260328T230000
DTSTAMP:20260328T230345
CREATED:20260123T150014Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260219T055752Z
UID:10000766-1774724400-1774738800@mickeysblackbox.com
SUMMARY:Solar Federation: A Tribute to Rush
DESCRIPTION:Saturday March 28th\, 2026\nDoors | 7:00 PM\nShow | 8:00 PM \nGeneral Admission Standing Room | $36.75 + Fees\nReserved Balcony & Mezzanine Seating | $38.80 + Fees \n+$5 on All Day of Show Purchases\nThis event is all ages – 21+ With Valid ID to Drink\nCome hungry! Snacks and light bites will be available at the canteen.\n—————————————————\nPresented by Mickey’s Black Box\n—————————————————\nSolar Federation:\nMike Bitts – bass\, keyboards\nFfej Herb – drums\, cymbals\, percussion\nJulie Schreiber – lead vocals\nEric Wirsing – guitar\, backing vocals \nHailing from Central Pennsylvania\, Solar Federation performs the music of Rush with passion and precision\, tuning into all the fine details die-hard fans analyze with every spin of an album. Formed in 2014\, the band spent an entire year honing its initial set list and rehearsing what is often called the most complex and difficult catalog of songs to perform in the pantheon of rock music. After a handful of live performances\, the band quickly established itself as one of the premier Rush tribute bands on the East Coast\, garnering praise from fans for its accurate interpretation of the material\, meticulous attention to detail\, and vocalist Julie Schreiber’s passionate delivery of Rush’s dynamic melodies and thought-provoking lyrics. Over the last nine years\, Solar Federation has become known as a faithful tribute to the music of Rush and has garnered respect among the vast community of Rush fans around the globe. \nFollowing the death of Peart\, Solar Federation was invited to perform at A Night for Neil\, a memorial tribute concert organized by Peart’s parents and family as well as the nonprofit organization\, Overtime Angels. The concert was held in Peart’s hometown of St. Catharines\, Ontario\, at the Meridian Center on Saturday\, October 22\, 2022. Solar Federation was the only Rush tribute band from the United States invited to perform. The band headlined the event with an hour-long closing set that brought down the house of more than 4\,000 fans. \nIn late 2023\, Solar Federation had the tremendous honor of collaborating with Rush’s longtime album cover artist\, Hugh Syme\, and legendary record producer\, Terry Brown\, on a studio version of “Witch Hunt” from Rush’s 1981 masterpiece\, Moving Pictures. The track premiered on April 12\, 2024\, on 97.3 WRVV The River and is available on all major streaming platforms. It will also appear on the forthcoming Songs for Neil: Volume 5\, set to release internationally on September 12\, 2024. The band’s live versions of “The Necromancer” and “Chemistry” have appeared on the previous Songs for Neil tribute albums\, with proceeds of sales benefitting Cancer Support Scotland (UK) and Glioblastoma Foundation Neil Peart research Award (USA). \nSolar Federation was voted “Best Tribute Band” at the 2023 Central PA Music Awards\, an accolade it also received in 2021 and for which it was nominated in 2022. \n“You can’t fake it with this band\,” said Ffej Herb\, Solar Federation’s drummer. “Rush fans are incredibly loyal and know this music inside and out.” \nRush is widely recognized for its legions of devoted fans from all corners of the world. “I’m constantly floored to learn that fans from all over the Mid-Atlantic region travel to attend our shows\,” said Herb. “To me\, that not only speaks volumes about the loyalty of Rush fans\, but it’s also a testament to the quality of our little band.” \nCheck out Solar Federation here!\nWebsite | Instagram | Facebook\n—————————————————\n*Ticket Alert*  \nTickets for Mickey’s Black Box are sold through TicketMaster\, via our website\, or in person at our Box Office. Any tickets purchased elsewhere will not be honored and we are not responsible for tickets purchased from any 3rd party sellers.  Do not google the name of the band to search for tickets.  Go to Mickeysblackbox.com ONLY. Mickeysblackbox.com will never direct you anywhere but the official TicketMaster event site. \n\nAll bags are subject are to search upon entry. Tickets are non-refundable\, save for instances in which performances are cancelled by Mickey’s Black Box. For more information about our venue or to make an ADA request\, please visit the FAQ page of our website: https://mickeysblackbox.com/faq/ or call our box office line at (717) 723 – 8463.
URL:https://mickeysblackbox.com/event/solar-federation-a-tribute-to-rush/
LOCATION:Mickey’s Black Box\, 101 Rock Lititz Boulevard\, Lititz\, PA\, 17543\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mickeysblackbox.com/app/uploads/2026/01/Solar-Federation-2026-Updated-e1771480660298.jpeg
END:VEVENT
