X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Saint James Lancaster": "https://www.saintjameslancaster.org/event/ignatian-spirituality/2026-03-31/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:saintjameslancaster
X-SOURCE:Saint James Lancaster
X-SOURCE-URL:https://www.saintjameslancaster.org/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260331T171500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260331T181500
DTSTAMP:20260328T230351
CREATED:20250728T180636Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20250728T180845Z
UID:10070927-1774977300-1774980900@www.saintjameslancaster.org
SUMMARY:Ignatian Spirituality
DESCRIPTION:Ignatian Spirituality\nTuesday evenings from 5:15 – 6:15 PM\nSeptember 9 – April 28\, 2026\nIgnatian spirituality is a way of living spirituality in everyday life. It asserts that God is present in our world and actively involved in our lives. It is a pathway to deeper prayer\, good decisions guided by keen discernment and an active life of service to others. \nThis 34-week program is designed for individuals who wish to commit to personal transformation by encountering God and deepening their experience of the divine. It will involve a daily and weekly commitment to spiritual practices with help and support from spiritual director Pat Latshaw. \nThe book\, The Ignatian Adventure by Kevin O’Brien will be used for discussion and to guide the group’s approach to spiritual growth with techniques that have been in use for almost 500 years. \nThe cost is $875 for 34 sessions. Scholarships are available. \nHave questions about scholarships and/or Ignatian Spirituality? Click here to email Pat Latshaw. \nClick here to register for the course.
URL:https://www.saintjameslancaster.org/event/ignatian-spirituality/2026-03-31/
LOCATION:Saint James Parish House Library
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.saintjameslancaster.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-HOME-Page-copy.jpg
END:VEVENT
