BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/spotting-signs-how-you-can-help-end-human-trafficking-157496"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Spotting the Signs: How You Can Help End Human Trafficking
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260331T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260331T194500
UID:e5fac8da7d5f765cc4e30cdda9c343dc@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, Presentation\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nHuman trafficki
 ng is a global epidemic that exists right here in our own communities\, of
 ten hiding in plain sight. Join us for an essential session with Barb Bing
 ham from the YWCA Greater Harrisburg and PAATH15 Crossroads on the realiti
 es of modern-day slavery. This session will cover how trafficking operates
  along major corridors like Route 15\, the tactics used by traffickers to 
 exploit the vulnerable\, and how the YWCA provides life-saving services to
  survivors. Gain the knowledge needed to understand this complex issue and
  learn how our community is fighting back.Whether you are a neighbor\, a l
 ocal leader\, or a professional on the front lines\, your presence matters
 .Get the tools to: ✅ Identify the hidden signs ✅ Respond safely and ef
 fectively ✅ Support a thriving\, protected community.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Morgan Center B
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/spotting-signs-how-you-c
 an-help-end-human-trafficking-157496
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
