DESCRIPTION:Arts & Crafts\, Community\, Health & Wellness\, Storytime\, To
 ddlers\, Children\n\nWe pause our family storytimes for this five week Pla
 y and Learn program tailored to children who are approaching kindergarten 
 age. Enjoy the play centers we have set out\, along with a story and craft
  - just enough structure to get your child some practice with group learni
 ng but with caregivers at their side for support! We will also have early 
 intervention experts on the side each week to provide information in case 
 you have questions about your child's development. For ages 3-6 with paren
 t or caregiver.Weekly topics:March 18: Early Literacy with Quarryville Lib
 rary Youth staff plus FREE vision care screenings courtesy of Vision Corps
 March 25: Speech and Language Development with Lancaster County Interventi
 on April 1: Growth and Development with Thrive to Five / Parents as Teache
 rsApril 8: Pediatric Nutrition with Penn State ExtensionApril 15: Music an
 d Movement plus "Touch-a-Truck" ambulance and Family Safety with Wakefield
  EMS
