SUMMARY:Fact vs Fiction: The Reality of a Missing Persons Investigation
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260406T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260406T194500
UID:6a0303f9f2db3205bd57cae7430049ce@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, Presentation\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nWe've all read 
 it in novels and watched it on TV: a person vanishes and a lone detective 
 solves the case in 48 hours. But what actually happens when a Pennsylvania
 n goes missing? Join us for an evening with State Trooper James Grothey an
 d officers from the Manheim Township Police Department as they pull back t
 he curtain on the real-world investigative process.From the critical first
  hours and to the role of digital forensics and community alerts\, learn h
 ow law enforcement navigates the complexities of search and recovery. Disc
 over the truth behind "The First 48\," the legal hurdles of the job\, and 
 how real life is much more intricate than fiction. Registration is encoura
 ged
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Morgan Center B
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/reserved-adult-services-
 program-161151
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
