X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/short-story-discussion-group-147880"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Short Story Discussion Group
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260407T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260407T150000
UID:dccf85751463c7e15d2d462f358903f8@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Book Club\, Discussion\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nJoin us on the fi
 rst Tuesday of each month as we read and discuss works in the Short Story 
 genre! From classic to contemporary\, we’ll cover a variety of authors a
 nd stories to help us explore well-known works and introduce us to new fav
 orites.  2026 Reading List:January 6: “A Very Old Man with Enormous Wing
 s” by Gabriel García MárquezFebruary 3: “A Sound of Thunder” by Ra
 y BradburyMarch 3: “A Biography” by Penelope LivelyApril 7: “Better 
 Living Through Algorithms” by Naomi KritzerMay 5: “A Temporary Matter
 ” and “Mrs. Sen’s” by Jhumpa LahiriJune 2: “The Harvest” by Am
 y HempelJuly 7: “Mr. Death” by Alix E. HarrowAugust 4: “The Sniper
 ” by Liam O’FlahertySeptember 1: “How to Pronounce Knife\,” “Chi
 ck-A-Chee\,” and “Edge of the World” by Souvankham ThammavongsaOctob
 er 6: “The Summer People” by Shirley JacksonNovember 3: “The Lottery
  Ticket” by Anton Chekhov and “Contents of the Dead Man’s Pocket” 
 by Jack FinneyDecember 1: “The Burglar’s Christmas” by Willa Cather 
 (under the pseudonym “Elizabeth L. Seymour”)For assistance finding cop
 ies of each story\, please contact the library at 717-394-2651 ext. 1350 o
 r askus@lancasterpubliclibrary.org.Registration is encouraged but not requ
 ired!
LOCATION:Lancaster\, LPL Board Room
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/short-story-discussion-g
 roup-147880
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
