SUMMARY:The Making of "The Quiet Gospel"
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260408T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260408T194500
UID:eb0a9d4370ab9fe9171f19e5a85f8393@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, Discussion\, Presentation\, Adults\n\nJoin Mount J
 oy native and local author Rodney Garber for a collaborative discussion an
 d book signing of his book The Quiet Gospel.The book outlines 21 principle
 s for living and loving like Jesus in a loud and offended world\, inviting
  readers to consider a simple but powerful question:What if the loudest wa
 y to share our faith was simply to live it quietly?During the event\, Rodn
 ey will also share the story behind the book—how it came to be written\,
  the unexpected journey of putting it together\, and the ups and downs of 
 writing a book he never originally intended to write.Through reflection an
 d practical insight\, Rodney explores how character\, consistency\, humili
 ty\, and everyday interactions can reflect the life and example of Christ.
  Rather than focusing on louder voices\, The Quiet Gospel points to a quie
 ter\, relational approach to faith—one lived out through how we treat pe
 ople and engage the world around us.The event will include a short discuss
 ion\, time for questions and conversation\, and an opportunity to meet the
  author and have a copy of the book signed.Registration Required
LOCATION:Milanof-Schock
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/making-quiet-gospel-1682
 47
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
