X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Oh\, Deer! a Lancaster Parks program
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260409T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260409T190000
UID:c7f80eabb339ce1729e66ebba83c5f7a@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, Presentation\, STEM\, Children\, Tweens\, Teens\, 
 Adults\, Seniors\n\nBest for adults and older children. Please register al
 l attendees.White-tailed deer are the most widely distributed large animal
  in North America. The declining interest in large game hunting has the de
 er population going mostly unchecked which is not a good thing for young n
 ative trees trying to grow. Learn interesting facts about deer during this
  program where you will get to see and touch an impressive deer skull\, pe
