BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/parachute-play-148188"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Parachute Play
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T101500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T104500
UID:611b64ba0d1f0a90f7113d9b4f36b616@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Toddlers\, Children\n\nJoin us for a cooperative m
 ovement program where we will use our imaginations while we play with a pa
 rachute! Stories and songs will be incorporated\, while we move about and 
 use our motor skills. A great activity for young children and their adults
  to come together and share an exciting and engaging play experience! (For
  safety reasons\, children must not be younger than 18 months or older tha
 n 3 years old with an adult\, adult involvement is required)Adults attendi
 ng with their child(ren) do NOT need to register. Please add any additiona
 l registrants to your registration if more than one child that will be par
 ticipating in the program.Registration will open at 9:00AM on April 1st fo
 r Manheim Township and East Lampeter residents and on Friday\, April 3rd f
 or residents of other municipalities.Storytime PoliciesNo Show – Patrons
  failing to cancel their registration for more than 2 library programs in 
 a month will be restricted from registering for future programs for a peri
 od of one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hour
 s prior to the start of the program to allow for those on the waiting list
  to be notified of their change in registration status.Late Arrivals – P
 lease arrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for par
 king and other circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the desig
 nated time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wai
 t list who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be all
 owed into the program. However\, registrants will not be permitted to ente
 r the program 5 minutes past the start time.Accompanying Adults – This p
 rogram is for adults and children to enjoy together. Please plan to attend
  and be engaged with your child. Drop offs will not be permitted.Cancellat
 ions- Please check your email prior to departing to verify that the progra
 m has not been cancelled.Program Limits - Patrons are limited to one sessi
 on of multiple session programs per week.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Lapp Story Silo
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/parachute-play-148188
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
