  with us at Quarryville Library for our certified Family Place program! Tw
 o programs each week\, differentiated by child’s age. If you have childr
 en in both groups\, you may participate in both or choose a different one 
 each week to get the maximum benefit!10 am-11 am –  Parent-child worksho
 p (birth to 3 with caregiver) -providing a welcoming community environment
  with resources that families need to nurture their children’s developme
 nt to help ensure they enter school ready and able to learn.Weekly topics:
 March 18: Early Literacy with Quarryville Library Youth staff plus FREE vi
 sion care screenings courtesy of Vision CorpsMarch 25: Speech and Language
  Development with Lancaster County Intervention April 1: Growth and Develo
 pment with Thrive to Five / Parents as TeachersApril 8: Pediatric Nutritio
 n with Penn State ExtensionApril 15: Music and Movement plus "Touch-a-Truc
 k" ambulance and Family Safety with Wakefield EMSEach week offers opportun
 ities for children to play with developmentally appropriate toys in a play
  group setting and for parents to meet and question community experts in t
 he areas of child development\, speech and language\, nutrition\, play\, m
 ovement\, and music.Learn more about what it means to be a Family Place li
 brary on our website!
LOCATION:Quarryville\, QVL C.X. Carlson Cultural Room
