BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/your-street-trees-and-urban-forest-170090"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Your Street Trees and the Urban Forest
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260418T113000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260418T121500
UID:76a3bb25d40ed5085f27a31e65fc5824@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, Teens\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nTrees are critically i
 mportant to our living in a healthy city\, not just in parks and yards\, b
 ut also along the streets and alleys. Through this presentation you will b
 e introduced to the benefits of street trees\, including environmental\, e
 conomic\, and social impacts. Learn how the City of Lancaster addresses co
 mmon urban tree challenges such as pests/diseases\, development\, and the 
 importance of community involvement in tree preservation. Audience members
  will take part in activities that will help them identify trees\, how to 
 report tree issues\, and better understand the City’s municipal tree pol
 icies. By better understanding the unique environment of the City\, our ur
 ban forest will remain healthy and verdant\, and continue to benefit all r
 esidents and visitors long into the future.All ages · Walk-ins welcome!
LOCATION:Lancaster\, LPL Board Room
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/your-street-trees-and-ur
 ban-forest-170090
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
