DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260421T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260421T193000
UID:f3522fd25ffa36c4a1f177598039468e@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Movie & Film\, Teens\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nAcross the U.S.\, l
 ibrarians face the impact of uniting against library collection standards 
 that include restrictions on race-related and LGBTQIA+ content. Drawing on
  historical context\, “The Librarians” explores the broader implicatio
 ns for education and public life. Join us for an in-depth look at the figh
 t against libraries and how book review policies are shaping their communi
 ties. Ages 16+.
LOCATION:Ephrata\, EPH Multipurpose Room
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/librarians-film-150700
