  to explore and learn about insects\, including building bugs with playdoh
 !This program is intended for children 3-6 years old. Children should be a
 ble to listen to\, comprehend and participate in emergent science\, math a
 nd literacy topics. Activities may include small parts so children should 
 be past the stage of mouthing items. Parents and caregivers are invited to
  participate with their children to learn how to replicate the activities 
 at home!Sensory experiences provide children with opportunities to develop
  fine motor skills\, eye-hand coordination\, problem solving\, logic and c
 oncentration. They'll grow their attention spans and practice emotional re
 gulation and mindfulness.Allergy notice: Please note sensory materials may
  contain allergens like wheat.Ms. Laura has over 20 years of preschool cla
 ssroom experience bringing a wealth of knowledge in early childhood develo
 pment. Her approach focuses on creating a warm\, engaging\, and supportive
  environment where children can thrive.Adults attending with their child(r
 en) do NOT need to register. Please add any additional registrants to your
  registration if more than one child that will be participating in the pro
 gram.Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, April 8th for Manheim
  Township and East Lampeter residents and on Friday\, April 10th for resid
 ents of other municipalities.Storytime PoliciesNo Show – Patrons failing
  to cancel their registration for more than 2 library programs in a month 
 will be restricted from registering for future programs for a period of on
 e month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hours prior 
 to the start of the program to allow for those on the waiting list to be n
 otified of their change in registration status.Late Arrivals – Please ar
 rive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for parking and
  other circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the designated ti
 me. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wait list w
 ho will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be allowed int
 o the program. However\, registrants will not be permitted to enter the pr
 ogram 5 minutes past the start time.Accompanying Adults – This program i
 s for adults and children to enjoy together. Please plan to attend and be 
 engaged with your child. Drop offs will not be permitted.Cancellations- Pl
 ease check your email prior to departing to verify that the program has no
 t been cancelled.
