X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/kids-garden-club-170440"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Kids' Garden Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T174500
UID:1cecf27596c4ed020e8e565ef4769268@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Children\n\nSpring has sprung and it's time for so
 me garden fun!  Join us on the on our patio for our exciting garden time! 
  (Rain or shine - if it's raining\, we'll be meeting indoors and limit out
  outside time.)  We'll read some stories\, do some crafts\, and of course\
 , get our hands in that soil and plant some seeds!  ***This week we'll exp
 lore the different parts of a plant -starting at a seed!  And we'll spend 
 some time with our newly planted seeds in the pots.***We'll supply the see
 ds\, the tools\, and the planters - you supply your own gloves.  Plan on g
 etting a little dirty.  This program is for children ages 6 - 9 years old.
   Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, April 8th for Manheim To
 wnship and East Lampeter residents and on Wednesday\, April 15th for resid
 ents of other municipalities.Library Program Policies No Show – Patron
 s failing to cancel their registration for more than 2 library programs in
  a month will be restricted from registering for future programs for a per
 iod of one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hou
 rs prior to the start of the program to allow those on the waiting list to
  be notified of their change in registration status. Late Arrivals – P
 lease arrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for
  parking and other circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the d
 esignated time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the
  wait list who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be
  allowed into the program. However\, registrants will not be permitted
  to enter the program 5 minutes past the start time. Drop Off Program –
  This program is intended for children over the age of 6 years who can p
 articipate independently. Adult(s) must be present to check in child with 
 youth services staff prior to program. Adults will not be allowed in the e
 vent space.  *For children ages 6–7\, this is a drop-off program\; h
 owever\, a parent or caregiver must remain nearby and wait outside the p
 rogram room for the duration of the program. Photography The Manheim Tow
 nship Public Library Code of Conduct Policy prohibits photographing or vid
 eo recording individuals (including children) without their consent (or in
  the case of a child\, the consent of a parent or guardian).
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Patio
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/kids-garden-club-170440
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
