BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/parachute-play-148190"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Parachute Play
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260424T101500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260424T104500
UID:521f721122e97ab596f4d0b44ad7abfe@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Toddlers\, Children\n\nJoin us for a cooperative m
 ovement program where we will use our imaginations while we play with a pa
 rachute! Stories and songs will be incorporated\, while we move about and 
 use our motor skills. A great activity for young children and their adults
  to come together and share an exciting and engaging play experience! (For
  safety reasons\, children must not be younger than 18 months or older tha
 n 3 years old with an adult\, adult involvement is required)Adults attendi
 ng with their child(ren) do NOT need to register. Please add any additiona
 l registrants to your registration if more than one child that will be par
 ticipating in the program.Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, 
 April 15th for Manheim Township and East Lampeter residents and on Friday\
 , April 17th for residents of other municipalities.Storytime PoliciesNo Sh
 ow – Patrons failing to cancel their registration for more than 2 librar
 y programs in a month will be restricted from registering for future progr
 ams for a period of one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations a
 t least 2 hours prior to the start of the program to allow for those on th
 e waiting list to be notified of their change in registration status.Late 
 Arrivals – Please arrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to
  allow for parking and other circumstances. The program will begin promptl
 y at the designated time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to th
 ose on the wait list who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registra
 nts may be allowed into the program. However\, registrants will not be per
 mitted to enter the program 5 minutes past the start time.Accompanying Adu
 lts – This program is for adults and children to enjoy together. Please 
 plan to attend and be engaged with your child. Drop offs will not be permi
 tted.Cancellations- Please check your email prior to departing to verify t
 hat the program has not been cancelled.Program Limits - Patrons are limite
 d to one session of multiple session programs per week.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Lapp Story Silo
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/parachute-play-148190
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
