SUMMARY:Teen Book Talk: A Little Princess
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260427T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260427T190000
UID:2257c6829ddd2b42587902e43b510eba@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Book Club\, Teens\n\nFor Teens ages 13-18 years of age only.Ca
 lling all teen readers! Join us for Teen Book Talk\, a fun and engaging mo
 nthly book discussion group led by members of our Teen Advisory Board! Boo
 k selections are chosen by teens during advisory meetings. Interested in j
 oining the Teen Advisory Board? Sign up through the library calendar. Each
  month\, we’ll dive into a new title—ranging from trending young adult
  fiction to graphic novels\, fantasy epics\, thought-provoking contemporar
 y stories\, and more.This month we'll be reading "A Little Princess" by Fr
 ances Hodgson. Sara Crewe looks like a princess as she enters boarding sch
 ool - she wears beautiful clothes and has the best manners.  But what happ
 ens when all of the money disappears and Sara is left with nothing?  She i
 s forced to sleep in the attic of the school and is wearing rags.  Can Sar
 a overcome this "riches to rags" turn of events and come out as the prince
 ss she knows she is in the end? You’ll get the chance to share your thou
 ghts\, hear different perspectives\, and connect with fellow book lovers i
 n a relaxed and welcoming space. Snacks will be provided\, and occasionall
 y we’ll have themed activities or giveaways tied to the book!Note: To he
 lp everyone stay present and get the most out of the experience\, we ask t
 hat all phones stay in pockets or bags during the program. Thank you for y
 our cooperation!Library Program PoliciesNo Show – Patrons failing to can
 cel their registration for more than 2 library programs in a month will be
  restricted from registering for future programs for a period of one month
 ’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hours prior to the 
 start of the program to allow for those on the waiting list to be notified
  of their change in registration status.Late Arrivals – Please arrive 10
  minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for parking and other 
 circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the designated time. At 
 this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wait list who will
  be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be allowed into the p
 rogram. However\, registrants will not be permitted to enter the program 5
  minutes past the start time.Check In - All participants must provide an e
 mergency contact number upon registration or at the start of the program.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Study Room #119
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/teen-book-talk-156957
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
