DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Toddlers\n\nA time for Toddlers with their grown-u
 p\, dedicated to stories\, discovery and exploring!  (18 months to 36 mont
 hs\, with adult. Other family members welcome.)Adults attending with their
  child(ren) do NOT need to register. Please add any additional registrants
  to your registration if more than one child that will be participating in
  the program.Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, April 15th fo
 r Manheim Township and East Lampeter residents and on Friday\, April 17th 
 for residents of other municipalities.Storytime PoliciesNo Show – Patron
 s failing to cancel their registration for more than 2 library programs in
  a month will be restricted from registering for future programs for a per
 iod of one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hou
 rs prior to the start of the program to allow for those on the waiting lis
 t to be notified of their change in registration status.Late Arrivals – 
 Please arrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for pa
 rking and other circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the desi
 gnated time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wa
 it list who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be al
 lowed into the program. However\, registrants will not be permitted to ent
 er the program 5 minutes past the start time.Accompanying Adults – This 
 program is for adults and children to enjoy together. Please plan to atten
 d and be engaged with your child. Drop offs will not be permitted.Cancella
 tions- Please check your email prior to departing to verify that the progr
 am has not been cancelled.Program Limits - Patrons are limited to one sess
 ion of multiple session programs per week.
