BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Stevens & Smith Center": "https://stevensandsmithcenter.org/event/first-look-fete/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:stevensandsmithcenter
X-SOURCE:Stevens & Smith Center
X-SOURCE-URL:https://stevensandsmithcenter.org/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260501T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260501T213000
DTSTAMP:20260328T230353
CREATED:20260313T204542Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260323T221654Z
UID:10000026-1777656600-1777671000@stevensandsmithcenter.org
SUMMARY:[SOLD OUT]The First Look Fête
DESCRIPTION:THIS EVENT IS SOLD OUT \nInterest in the event was overwhelming and the event sold out very quickly. Thank you for your interest! There are more ways to celebrate the Stevens & Smith Center Grand Opening. Consider joining us for the Ribbon Cutting Ceremony or the Community Block Party for History! \n————————————————————– \nFriday evening culminates in an elegant\, high-end cocktail celebration honoring the extraordinary generosity and bold vision that brought the Stevens & Smith Center to life. This exclusive\, ticketed event brings together our closest supporters for a night of gratitude and recognition\, just next door in the newly renovated Commons on Vine.\n\nGuests will enjoy curated cocktails\, elevated fare\, lively entertainment\, and one of the very first opportunities to experience the Center up close. It’s more than a party\, it’s a toast to the partners and donors who made history possible\, and a sparkling first look at what’s ahead.\n\nSOLD OUT\nDress & Schedule of Events \nDress for the First Look Fête is cocktail attire. The schedule of events is as follows: \n\n\n 	5:30pm: Cocktails and lavish bites\n\n 	7:00pm: Program and performances\n 	7:30pm: Dessert and music\n\n… and then we welcome you inside the Stevens & Smith Center for first looks!
URL:https://stevensandsmithcenter.org/event/first-look-fete/
LOCATION:Commons on Vine\, Lancaster County Convention Center\, 19 E. Vine Street\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17602
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://stevensandsmithcenter.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Sold-Out-Fete_Web.png
END:VEVENT
