 p opportunity for teens to shape library programs\, services\, and spaces!
 As a member\, you’ll:📚 Help plan and promote exciting teen events💡
  Provide input on books\, technology\, and programs you want to see🎤 De
 velop leadership skills and gain volunteer experience🤝 Make friends and
  connect with your communityWe’re looking for passionate\, creative\, an
 d motivated teens (ages 13 - 18) who want to have a voice in making the li
 brary an awesome place for young people.Meetings: Once a month at the libr
 aryPerks: Gain leadership experience\, make an impact\, and if you choose 
 to become a library volunteer\, you can earn volunteer hours!Program Polic
 iesDrop Off Program – This program is intended for children over the age
  of 13 years who can participate independently. Adult(s) must check in wit
 h library staff to provide an emergency contact at their first meeting. Ad
 ults will not be allowed in the event space. Designated Ages – Please ad
 here to the age restrictions designated on your registration. Only childre
 n in that age range will be admitted.
