DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Toddlers\n\nA time for Toddlers with their grown-u
 p\, dedicated to stories\, discovery and exploring!  (18 months to 36 mont
 hs\, with adult. Other family members welcome.)Adults attending with their
  child(ren) do NOT need to register. Please add any additional registrants
  to your registration if more than one child that will be participating in
  the program.Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, April 29th fo
 r Manheim Township and East Lampeter residents and on Friday\, May 1st for
  residents of other municipalities.Storytime PoliciesNo Show – Patrons f
 ailing to cancel their registration for more than 2 library programs in a 
 month will be restricted from registering for future programs for a period
  of one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hours 
 prior to the start of the program to allow for those on the waiting list t
 o be notified of their change in registration status.Late Arrivals – Ple
 ase arrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for parki
 ng and other circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the designa
 ted time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wait 
 list who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be allow
 ed into the program. However\, registrants will not be permitted to enter 
 the program 5 minutes past the start time.Accompanying Adults – This pro
 gram is for adults and children to enjoy together. Please plan to attend a
 nd be engaged with your child. Drop offs will not be permitted.Cancellatio
 ns- Please check your email prior to departing to verify that the program 
 has not been cancelled.Program Limits - Patrons are limited to one session
  of multiple session programs per week.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Lapp Story Silo
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/toddler-time-148696
