DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Children\n\nJoin Ms. Laura for a fun and engaging 
 preschool program designed to spark curiosity and a love for learning in y
 oung children! This program features stories\, songs\, and hands-on activi
 ties tailored for preschool-aged kids. Each session focuses on building ea
 rly literacy\, motor skills\, and social interaction through playful explo
 ration.Perfect for ages 3–6 with an adult\, this program provides a welc
 oming and inclusive environment where kids can learn and grow together. Pa
 rents and caregivers are encouraged to participate and share in the joy of
  discovery with their little ones.Ms. Laura has over 20 years of preschool
  classroom experience bringing a wealth of knowledge in early childhood de
 velopment. Her approach focuses on creating a warm\, engaging\, and suppor
 tive environment where children can thrive.Adults attending with their chi
 ld(ren) do NOT need to register. Please add any additional registrants to 
 your registration if more than one child that will be participating in the
  program.Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, April 29th for Ma
 nheim Township and East Lampeter residents and on Friday\, May 1st for res
 idents of other municipalities.Storytime PoliciesNo Show – Patrons faili
 ng to cancel their registration for more than 2 library programs in a mont
 h will be restricted from registering for future programs for a period of 
 one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hours prio
 r to the start of the program to allow for those on the waiting list to be
  notified of their change in registration status.Late Arrivals – Please 
 arrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for parking a
 nd other circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the designated 
 time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wait list
  who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be allowed i
 nto the program. However\, registrants will not be permitted to enter the 
 program 5 minutes past the start time.Accompanying Adults – This program
  is for adults and children to enjoy together. Please plan to attend and b
 e engaged with your child. Drop offs will not be permitted.Cancellations- 
 Please check your email prior to departing to verify that the program has 
 not been cancelled.Program Limits - Patrons are limited to one session of 
 multiple session programs per week.Preschool Party Registration Requiremen
 ts – All children who will be participating in the craft will need to be
  registered as a participant to allow for adequate supplies.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Lapp Story Silo
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/preschool-party-148762
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
