BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/dungeons-and-dragons-adventure-club-kids-ages-9-12-only-2-168861"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Dungeons and Dragons Adventure Club for Kids (Ages 9-12 only) #2
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260513T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260513T183000
UID:1232d5243e8d60c6f6167dbb84030a3c@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Gaming\, Children\, Tweens\n\nTo ensure fair access for as man
 y families as possible\, please read the registration guidelines for this 
 program.One Session Per Month: Patrons may register for only one session o
 f this program per month.Duplicate Registrations: Registrations for more t
 han one session in the same month will be cancelled.We appreciate your und
 erstanding as we work to provide equitable access to this popular program.
 Calling all young adventurers ages 9 to 12! Join us for an exciting journe
 y into the world of Dungeons & Dragons\, where your imagination sets the c
 ourse. Together\, we’ll learn how to create unique characters\, navigate
  magical lands\, and solve thrilling quests. No prior experience is needed
 —new and experienced players alike are welcome!In each session\, you'll 
 explore stories full of mystery\, monsters\, and more all while working as
  a team to overcome challenges and puzzles. Whether you're a brave warrior
 \, a clever wizard\, or a sneaky rogue\, there’s always an adventure wai
 ting. Are you ready to roll the dice and discover where the story leads?Sp
 aces are limited\, so sign up today to secure your spot in our grand adven
 ture! All materials will be provided.Registration will open at 9:00AM on W
 ednesday\, April 29th for Manheim Township and East Lampeter residents and
  on Wednesday\, May 6th for residents of other municipalities.LIBRARY PROG
 RAM POLICIES:Drop Off Program – This program is intended for children ov
 er the age of 9 years who can participate independently. Adult(s) must be 
 present to check in child with youth services staff prior to program. Adul
 ts will not be allowed in the event space. Designated Ages – Please adhe
 re to the age restrictions designated on your registration. Only children 
 in that age range will be admitted.Registration Requirements – To help u
 s manage our space\, please register every person who will be attending\, 
 including siblings.No Show – Patrons failing to cancel their registratio
 n for more than 2 library programs in a month will be restricted from regi
 stering for future programs for a period of one month’s time. Please can
 cel your registrations at least 2 hours prior to the start of the program 
 to allow for those on the waiting list to be notified of their change in r
 egistration status.Late Arrivals – Please arrive 10 minutes prior to the
  start of the program to allow for parking and other circumstances. The pr
 ogram will begin promptly at the designated time. At this time\, your spot
  will be forfeited to those on the wait list who will be granted entry. If
  spots remain\, registrants may be allowed into the program. However\, reg
 istrants will not be permitted to enter the program 5 minutes past the sta
 rt time.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Morgan Center A
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/dungeons-and-dragons-adv
 enture-club-kids-ages-9-12-only-2-168861
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/kids-garden-club-170441"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Kids' Garden Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260513T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260513T174500
UID:2fa07940b128c1988170b3567c8c45bf@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Children\n\nSpring has sprung and it's time for so
 me garden fun!  Join us on the on our patio for our exciting garden time! 
  (Rain or shine - if it's raining\, we'll be meeting indoors and limit out
  outside time.)  We'll read some stories\, do some crafts\, and of course\
 , get our hands in that soil and plant some seeds!  ***This week we'll be 
 exploring how to plant a rainbow and we'll be painting our very own pot.  
 We'll also get our hands dirty as we continue to take care of our plants i
 n the planter.***We'll supply the seeds\, the tools\, and the planters - y
 ou supply your own gloves.  Plan on getting a little dirty.  This program 
 is for children ages 6 - 9 years old.  Registration will open at 9:00AM on
  Wednesday\, April 29th for Manheim Township and East Lampeter residents a
 nd on Wednesday\, May 6th for residents of other municipalities.Library Pr
 ogram Policies No Show – Patrons failing to cancel their registration 
 for more than 2 library programs in a month will be restricted from regist
 ering for future programs for a period of one month’s time. Please cance
 l your registrations at least 2 hours prior to the start of the program to
  allow those on the waiting list to be notified of their change in registr
 ation status. Late Arrivals – Please arrive 10 minutes prior to th
 e start of the program to allow for parking and other circumstances. The p
 rogram will begin promptly at the designated time. At this time\, your spo
 t will be forfeited to those on the wait list who will be granted entry. I
 f spots remain\, registrants may be allowed into the program. However\, re
 gistrants will not be permitted to enter the program 5 minutes past th
 e start time. Drop Off Program – This program is intended for children
  over the age of 6 years who can participate independently. Adult(s) must 
 be present to check in child with youth services staff prior to program. A
 dults will not be allowed in the event space.  *For children ages 6–
 7\, this is a drop-off program\; however\, a parent or caregiver must re
 main nearby and wait outside the program room for the duration of the pr
 ogram. Photography The Manheim Township Public Library Code of Conduct Pol
 icy prohibits photographing or video recording individuals (including chil
 dren) without their consent (or in the case of a child\, the consent of a 
 parent or guardian).
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Patio
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/kids-garden-club-170441
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
