 \, Seniors\, Everyone\n\nOpen to all ages. This exhibit will run through M
 ay 1.We welcome this exhibit from the Octoraro Art Association. The OAA wa
 s founded in 1948 by local\, world-renowned artist Charles X. Carlson and 
 Oxford businessman John W. Roberts. Their objective was to enhance the cul
 ture of the Oxford area through exhibits\, art workshops\, and classes.The
  Octoraro Art Association continues its mission to this day. They are a gr
 oup of painters and potters who gather together sharing ideas and inspirat
 ion. They meet Thursdays from 1-3 pm at 5965 Forge Road in Oxford PA.
