BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"American Music Theatre": "https://amtshows.com/show/brothers-of-the-heart-2026/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:amtshows
X-SOURCE:American Music Theatre
X-SOURCE-URL:https://amtshows.com/events/
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260520
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260521
DTSTAMP:20260328T230355
CREATED:20250818T133055Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20250801T152137Z
UID:10001806-1779235200-1779321599@amtshows.com
SUMMARY:Brothers of the Heart
DESCRIPTION:Tickets: $39 $49 $59 $69\nAMT Member Pre-Sale: Wednesday\, August 20 at 10:00 a.m.\nPublic On-Sale: Friday\, August 22 at 10:00 a.m. \nWe are excited to welcome Brothers of the Heart back to American Music Theatre! \nSuper groups have a prestigious history in the music industry from such legendary rockers as The Traveling Wilburys to the iconic country foursome The Highwaymen to the stellar trio of Dolly Parton\, Emmylou Harris\, and Linda Ronstadt.  There’s a special excitement when successful artists combine their individual talents and star power to create something fresh and exciting.  That tradition continues with Brothers Of The Heart – Jimmy Fortune\, Bradley Walker\, Mike Rogers\, and Ben Isaacs – who reimagine country\, gospel\, and pop classics with their renditions of iconic songs such as “Ring of Fire\,” “Desperado\,” “Bye Bye Love\,” “Precious Memories\,” and more. \nFor certain concerts\, audience members may prefer to stand or dance\, especially when encouraged by the artist to do so. Guest expectations differ\, so we simply ask all attendees to extend mutual respect toward one another and maintain awareness of those around them. Our staff will only intervene in matters of safety or when behavior is deemed unruly\, combative\, or disruptive to the overall performance.
URL:https://amtshows.com/show/brothers-of-the-heart-2026/
LOCATION:American Music Theatre\, 2425 Lincoln Hwy East\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17605\, United States
CATEGORIES:Celebrity Concerts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://amtshows.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/BOH_Concessions-Events-and-News-for-Website-1920x1080-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
