UID:507e05ab794433721848654732439f5b@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Children\n\nJoin Ms. Laura for a fun and engaging 
 preschool program designed to spark curiosity and a love for learning in y
 oung children! This program features stories\, songs\, and hands-on activi
 ties tailored for preschool-aged kids. Each session focuses on building ea
 rly literacy\, motor skills\, and social interaction through playful explo
 ration.Perfect for ages 3–6 with an adult\, this program provides a welc
 oming and inclusive environment where kids can learn and grow together. Pa
 rents and caregivers are encouraged to participate and share in the joy of
  discovery with their little ones.Ms. Laura has over 20 years of preschool
  classroom experience bringing a wealth of knowledge in early childhood de
 velopment. Her approach focuses on creating a warm\, engaging\, and suppor
 tive environment where children can thrive.Adults attending with their chi
 ld(ren) do NOT need to register. Please add any additional registrants to 
 your registration if more than one child that will be participating in the
  program.Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, May 6th for Manhe
 im Township and East Lampeter residents and on Friday\, May 8th for reside
 nts of other municipalities.Storytime PoliciesNo Show – Patrons failing 
 to cancel their registration for more than 2 library programs in a month w
 ill be restricted from registering for future programs for a period of one
  month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hours prior t
 o the start of the program to allow for those on the waiting list to be no
 tified of their change in registration status.Late Arrivals – Please arr
 ive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for parking and 
 other circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the designated tim
 e. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wait list wh
 o will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be allowed into
  the program. However\, registrants will not be permitted to enter the pro
 gram 5 minutes past the start time.Accompanying Adults – This program is
  for adults and children to enjoy together. Please plan to attend and be e
 ngaged with your child. Drop offs will not be permitted.Cancellations- Ple
 ase check your email prior to departing to verify that the program has not
  been cancelled.Program Limits - Patrons are limited to one session of mul
 tiple session programs per week.Preschool Party Registration Requirements 
 – All children who will be participating in the craft will need to be re
 gistered as a participant to allow for adequate supplies.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Lapp Story Silo
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/preschool-party-148739
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
