BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/kids-garden-club-170442"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Kids' Garden Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260527T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260527T174500
UID:df4301441a50d5d7d6b331777acfc02d@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Children\n\nSpring has sprung and it's time for so
 me garden fun!  Join us on the on our patio for our exciting garden time! 
  (Rain or shine - if it's raining\, we'll be meeting indoors and limit out
  outside time.)  We'll read some stories\, do some crafts\, and of course\
 , get our hands in that soil and plant some seeds!  ***This week we'll tak
 e one final look at seeds with my favorite book "The Bad Seed".  We'll cre
 ate our very own "Bad Seed" and of course\, we'll get our hands dirty in o
 ur pots tending to our plants.***We'll supply the seeds\, the tools\, and 
 the planters - you supply your own gloves.  Plan on getting a little dirty
 .  This program is for children ages 6 - 9 years old.  Registration will o
 pen at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, May 13th for Manheim Township and East Lampet
 er residents and on Wednesday\, May 20th for residents of other municipali
 ties.Library Program Policies No Show – Patrons failing to cancel thei
 r registration for more than 2 library programs in a month will be restric
 ted from registering for future programs for a period of one month’s tim
 e. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hours prior to the start of
  the program to allow those on the waiting list to be notified of their ch
 ange in registration status. Late Arrivals – Please arrive 10 minutes
  prior to the start of the program to allow for parking and other circ
 umstances. The program will begin promptly at the designated time. At this
  time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wait list who will be 
 granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be allowed into the progr
 am. However\, registrants will not be permitted to enter the program 5
  minutes past the start time. Drop Off Program – This program is inten
 ded for children over the age of 6 years who can participate independently
 . Adult(s) must be present to check in child with youth services staff pri
 or to program. Adults will not be allowed in the event space.  *For chil
 dren ages 6–7\, this is a drop-off program\; however\, a parent or car
 egiver must remain nearby and wait outside the program room for the du
 ration of the program. Photography The Manheim Township Public Library Cod
 e of Conduct Policy prohibits photographing or video recording individuals
  (including children) without their consent (or in the case of a child\, t
 he consent of a parent or guardian).
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Patio
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/kids-garden-club-170442
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
